# Cursor Orchestrator — Handoff Protocol

Every agent working on this project must write a handoff document to `docs/agent-handoffs/` before ending their session. Use the template below. Filename: `phase-XX-complete.md` (e.g. `phase-01-complete.md`) or a descriptive name if not phase-based.

## Required Format

```markdown
## Handoff: [Phase Name] → [Next Phase]
Date: YYYY-MM-DD
Agent: [e.g. Phase 1 implementation]
Status: COMPLETE | PARTIAL

### What Was Completed
- Bullet list of deliverables.

### Files Created (exact paths)
- cursor-orchestrator/package.json
- ...

### Files Modified (exact paths + what changed)
- docs/PROGRESS.md — Phase 1 checkboxes marked complete.

### Tests/Verification Done
- npm run build succeeded.
- Extension activated via F5.
- ...

### Open Issues (blocking)
- None | List blocking issues.

### Open Issues (non-blocking)
- None | List non-blocking issues.

### Exact Next Agent Instruction
You are the [role] agent. Your task is [specific task].
Do NOT touch: [list files or areas].
Success criteria: [measurable criteria].
Start by reading: docs/PROGRESS.md, docs/SCOPE.md, this file.
```

## Rules

1. Write the handoff before ending your session — not after.
2. Use exact paths; no relative or ambiguous references.
3. If status is PARTIAL, list exactly what remains and what the next agent must do first.
4. "Exact Next Agent Instruction" must be copy-pasteable; the next agent should be able to start without guessing.
